article.headline: Lamar 88, North Texas 72
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas (AP) -- Gil Goodrich scored 21 points and had six assists as Lamar beat North Texas 88-72 Saturday night. Lamar (3-0) outscored North Texas (1-1) 19-4 in the opening minutes and led 53-25 at the half. Lamar shot almost 60 percent from the floor in the first half while the Mean Green shot only 38 percent. A 9-0 run early in the second half gave Lamar a 23-point lead with 14:50 remaining. Raymond Anthony had 18 points, Teddy Davis added 17 and Jason Grant had 13 for the Cardinals. Marqus Mitchell led North Texas with 24 points and Michael Jones added 13.
